    <div class="col-lg-3">
      <h2>Full featured template engine</h2>
      <p>LavaCactus uses and extends Django's templating engine. If you've built sites using Django before, you'll feel right at home.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-3">
      <h2>Pretty URLs</h2>
      <p>LavaCactus can prettify URLs, so you can turn <code>/about.html</code> into a fancier <code>/about/</code> or just use <code>about.html</code>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-3">
      <h2>Minification & Fingerprinting</h2>
      <p>For maximum performance, LavaCactus can minify and fingerprint your static assets. As for your pages, LavaCactus will automatically compress them.</p>
   </div>

